features: The Roasting and Air Frying kit includes the 3” stainless-steel extender ring, the 10” enamel baking pan, the air fry basket and the 3” cooking rack.
The stainless-steel extender ring increases the capacity of your NuWave Primo so you can cook up to a 14lb turkey, 12lb. ham and large roasts with ease.
The 10” enamel baking pan is perfect for baking, roasting, sautéing, slow cooking and much more. The non-stick enamel coating means foods won’t stick and cleanup is easy. Its also dishwasher safe.
The stainless-steel air fry basket is designed for maximum air-flow so all your foods are done perfectly, with a golden crispy outside and tender inside, without oil!
The 3” cooking rack allows you to cook in layers so complete meals are fast and easy. Its dishwasher safe for easy cleaning.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The NuWave Difference For over two decades, we have truly lived up to our philosophy to “Live Well For Less” with each and every one of our products. We are driven by the pursuit of safe, green products that can improve the quality of life. Throughout the company history, we have been committed to exceeding industry-standard best practices regarding safety and product quality. We are focused on developing environmentally conscious appliances that are affordable for everyone, all built with the latest culinary technology. All research and development is done onsite at our corporate headquarters in Libertyville, IL. While the NuWave line has many imitators, we are leaders in developing products that promote efficiency and value while enhancing the customer's quality of life through a foundation of trust and dependability. Our customers are always our top priority, and we are absolutely dedicated to ensuring that everyone who comes to NuWave enjoys a positive experience. As a result, our flagship products, the NuWave Oven and NuWave Precision Induction Cooktop, have been enjoyed by millions of happy customers throughout the globe. With this experience and commitment to creating superior products that are affordable and make day-to-day life easier and healthier, we are proud to offer you the NuWave Primo Combo Grill Oven.

The Next Evolution In The NuWave Oven Revolution NuWave has been the proud maker of the top countertop oven in the world ever since we introduced the NuWave Oven nearly 20 years ago. But just because we've been the leader in smart, healthy countertop kitchen appliances in this time doesn't mean we've rested on our laurels. The NuWave Oven has evolved over the years to deliver a superior cooking experience. From digital controls to precise temperature control to superior dome design, each NuWave Oven we introduce is better than the last, which is why we're proud to offer the latest and greatest NuWave Oven yet with exclusive features you won't find anywhere else with the NuWave Primo Combo Grill Oven.

Smart Tech Cooking Technology The NuWave Primo starts by generating conduction heat in the Power Head like a conventional oven, sending heat directly onto your food from the top. Smart Tech Cooking Technology The NuWave Primo utilizes a fan in the Power Head to provide convection heat which ensures your food gets evenly cooked on all sides at once. Smart Tech Cooking Technology The NuWave Primo also creates infrared heat, a special type of heat that penetrates the surface of your food. By penetrating your food, the Primo can cook on the inside and outside simultaneously, ensuring the inside is fully cooked and delicious while the outside won’t burn or overcook. Smart Tech Cooking Technology The NuWave Primo features a unique non-stick Grill Plate which works in tandem with the Power Head to provide direct heat on the bottom of your food. This ensures that your food is cooked from all sides at once for perfectly crispy results without the need to turn or flip. Conduction Heat Convection Heat Infrared Heat Direct Contact Heat

Integrated Digital Temperature Probe The NuWave Primo comes with an integrated stainless steel digital temperature probe that controls the cooking cycle based on your food’s internal temperature rather than the oven temperature or cooking time. Adjustable in precise, 1˚ F increments, the probe turns off the unit when the set internal temperature is reached. You’ll never have to worry about overcooking or undercooking your meat, poultry or fish when you cook with the NuWave Primo. Intuitive Digital Controls The NuWave Primo is made with intuitive digital controls built right into the Power Head. Adjust your cooking temperature, set your cooking time, customize the top and bottom heat percentages and so much more all with the simple press of a button. The Primo includes a Preheat button to help ensure perfect results, a Sear button for crispy results and a Warm/Reheat button keep your food at the perfect temperature until you’re ready to eat. The NuWave Primo can truly do it all. Convenient Pre-Programmed Menu The NuWave Primo features 100 recipe presets already programmed into the smart Power Head. This means that with the simple press of a button, the Primo will automatically cook at just the right temperature for just the right amount of time for some of the most popular dishes. The Primo has presets for everything from broccoli to burgers to chicken breasts and even cookies. And if you want to program your own recipes into your Primo, you can do just that with the Primo's save your own custom recipes directly into the unit.

Healthier Results The NuWave Primo's heating process and unique design ensure that most of the high-calorie fats and oils drip off your foods while the more nutritious, flavorful natural juices remain intact. Plus the elevated Grill Rack ensures that these fat drippings remain in the Primo base, separate from your delicious food and off of your dinner plate. Safe Operation You can stop worrying about whether or not you turned off the oven when you cook with the NuWave Primo. Unlike conventional ovens, the Primo will automatically shut itself off once the timer reaches zero. Plus, the Primo is designed to keep the hot air inside the oven and not let it escape into your cooking space, greatly reducing the chance of accidental burns. Easy To Clean The NuWave Primo comes with a non-stick Grill Plate meaning you simple have to wipe it down with a damp cloth after using. All parts of the Primo easily separate for easy cleaning. Best of all, the Power Dome, Grill Plate and base are all dishwasher-safe. NuWave Cooking Club App Featuring recipes specifically written by NuWave chefs for the NuWave Primo, there’s a recipe here for virtually any occasion. Whether you’re a first-time cook or a seasoned pro, you’ll be able to prepare everything from delicious meals to healthy snacks to scrumptious desserts using the resources in this app.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exactly what I needed for large projects
reviews.reviewText: I was having problems when cooking larger items in my NuWave in that the top would scorch and the rest wasn't done through. But adding the extender ring allows me to cook tall casseroles with dinner rolls on top for longer and more thoroughly, and the rolls are done just right now. I also can cook a whole turkey in 2 1/2 hours with juicy meat all done, and a golden brown skin because the ring makes the oven just right for that. Also, the other accessories with the ring are interesting. I have yet to try the air fry basket, but think it will be great for making French fries.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good Addition to the Primo
reviews.reviewText: If you have a NuWave Primo, then I suggest you get the Extender Ring. You will not regret it.. You never know when you will want to cook something big like a turkey and find you out your NuWave is too small.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the investment
reviews.reviewText: I just got this as an add on to my NuWave oven. I really like the NuWave Primo as is, but this really does give it that little extra to push it completely over the top. The fry basket helps with all things 'fried'. Since is it air fried, the greasy oily taste usually associated with frying is gone. So, the solid flavors of the foods come through more completely.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars This accessory kit is helpful if you don't already have NuWave oven accessories.
reviews.reviewText: Since the NuWave Primo Grill oven does not include any accessories, this kit is helpful if you don't already have NuWave oven accessories. This kit includes an extender ring, an air fry basket, a baking pan, and a 3" cooking rack.The baking pan is the same as supplied with previous NuWave oven models. This pan works well for baking and for dual layer cooking in the oven. I suggest lining this pan with aluminum foil for anything other than baking cakes or baked goods. Baking meats, fish, or anything using oils would damage the finish in the pan. The 3" rack included is not quite as useful since it is a 3" rack no matter which way you turn it. It would be more useful if it provided two different heights rather than both the same. The 1"/3" rack supplied with previous models is much more useful. The 1"/3" rack from older models is a bit large to fit in this oven, but it can be made to work if you place it right in this oven. Personally, I don't care for the stainless extender ring as you can't see the food below it as you can with the clear extender ring. Unfortunately, the older clear extender ring does not fit this oven. I do like the included air fry basket that comes with this kit. It does a good job at air frying frozen french fries which is all that I've used it for so far. The fry basket is large enough that I have eliminated my air fryer.I hope this review was helpful for you, and I will update it if my opinion changes.

reviews.reviewText: Although my Nuwave Primo came with an extender ring, this one is about 2 inches taller. I roasted a whole chicken and this heght is needed. The enameled pan and the basket and rack are also very handy. I am glad I bought this set.
